name: A. Kevin and Combination Lock
input: InputEach test contains multiple test cases. The first line contains the number of test cases $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \le t \le 10^4$$$).The only line of each test case contains a positive integer $$$x$$$ ($$$1\leq x\leq 10^9$$$).
output: OutputFor each test case, output "YES" or "NO" (without quotes) in one line, representing whether Kevin can unlock the combination lock and escape. You can output the answer in any case (upper or lower). For example, the strings "yEs", "yes", "Yes", and "YES" will be recognized as positive responses.
